Buon Natale.

02:53.548 --> 02:55.091
Buon Natale.

02:56.467 --> 02:58.678
Buon Natale.

03:01.139 --> 03:02.807
(Sydney)'Now, we're ready to goto Chicago'

03:02.849 --> 03:04.559
because the mostimportant passenger

03:04.559 --> 03:05.935
on the flight just arrived.

03:06.060 --> 03:08.479
This is Leah,she's flying home to dad

03:08.521 --> 03:10.273
after seeingher grandparents.

03:10.315 --> 03:14.360
Hi, Leah. My name is Sydney.It's nice to meet you.

03:16.237 --> 03:17.780
[whispers]She's a little nervous.

03:17.822 --> 03:19.699
Thanks, Ted.I've got it from here.

03:20.867 --> 03:22.577
You don't look that nervousto me.

03:22.702 --> 03:24.245
In fact, you look likesomeone who knows

03:24.370 --> 03:28.541
that her private flying carpetis ready to take her home.

03:28.625 --> 03:30.043
'Let's get you settled.'

03:30.126 --> 03:32.045
And your backpack.

03:32.128 --> 03:33.129
Thank you.

03:34.088 --> 03:36.716
So, how was your visitwith your grandparents?

03:38.384 --> 03:42.096
Well, yeah. I bet your grandmamade you all your favorite food.

03:42.138 --> 03:45.099
And your grandpa probablytold you lots of funny stories?

03:45.183 --> 03:46.100
[giggling]

03:46.100 --> 03:47.894
Well, mine won't bequite as good.

03:47.977 --> 03:49.771
But I can get you foodand tell you stories too

03:49.854 --> 03:51.564
if you'd like,just after all the rest

03:51.648 --> 03:53.066
of the passengerstake their seats.

03:53.149 --> 03:55.860
And, then, later, whenthe seatbelt sign goes off

03:55.944 --> 03:59.656
we can go up front and takea peek at the view. Yeah?

03:59.781 --> 04:02.992
Now, we may not have Santa'sreindeer power under the hood

04:03.034 --> 04:07.747
but how would you like to flyalmost as fast?

04:07.830 --> 04:09.749
Buckle up, okay?I'll be right back.

04:09.791 --> 04:12.168
Hello. How do you do?

04:15.964 --> 04:18.841
(Sydney)'So, Leah, what's yourfavorite part of Christmas?'

04:18.882 --> 04:20.969
(Leah)'I think decorating the tree.'

04:21.052 --> 04:24.222
(Sydney)'In that case,I have an idea.'

04:24.305 --> 04:27.934
I bet you we have the onlyChristmas tree at 35,000 feet.

04:27.976 --> 04:30.436
Unless Santa had oneon his sleigh.

04:30.520 --> 04:33.314
But I doubt there's roomwith all the presents.

04:33.439 --> 04:34.941
[chuckles]That's a good point.

04:35.024 --> 04:36.818
But I like the wayyou're thinkin'.

04:36.943 --> 04:40.238
Sydney, what does..

04:40.321 --> 04:41.990
..."U-M" mean?

04:42.115 --> 04:45.535
"U-M" meansUnaccompanied Minor.

04:45.576 --> 04:49.122
Or a kid that's brave enoughto fly all by herself.

04:49.205 --> 04:50.707
Dad wanted to come.

04:50.832 --> 04:53.668
But he had a deadlinefrom his editor at the paper.

04:53.751 --> 04:54.836
Oh.

04:54.919 --> 04:57.297
Wanna see the Christmas presentI made him?

04:57.380 --> 04:58.506
I do.

04:58.631 --> 05:00.341
I made it for him with grandma.

05:00.466 --> 05:01.592
I hope he likes it.

05:01.676 --> 05:04.470
Aw. He is gonna love that.

05:04.512 --> 05:06.305
It's beautiful.What a treasure.

05:06.389 --> 05:08.725
You must have had a great visitwith your grandparents.

05:08.766 --> 05:12.603
Yeah. I even got to trymy mom's old roller skates.

05:12.645 --> 05:14.063
Oh, wow.

05:14.856 --> 05:17.275
My mom's an angel now.

05:20.361 --> 05:23.031
Hey. You know what?

05:23.031 --> 05:25.408
My mom's an angel now, too.

05:25.533 --> 05:27.326
But she's alwayswatching over me

05:27.410 --> 05:30.496
just like your mom'salways watching over you.

05:33.541 --> 05:35.251
And speaking of angels

05:35.293 --> 05:37.378
you know whatour Christmas tree needs?

05:37.378 --> 05:40.923
- Hm..- Wings.

05:41.716 --> 05:43.926
Yeah. Some wings.

05:45.928 --> 05:48.097
- What do you think?- It's perfect.

05:48.139 --> 05:48.890
It is perfect.

05:48.931 --> 05:51.225
[airplane alert beeps]

05:51.225 --> 05:53.436
Alright, Leah, I have to dothe food service now.

05:53.478 --> 05:57.231
In the meantime, why don't youjust enjoy the view?

05:59.901 --> 06:03.154
[instrumental music]

06:06.699 --> 06:09.577
Hurry, Sydney! Hurry!

06:09.702 --> 06:11.788
Wow, you're even fasterthan I am. Excuse us.

06:11.829 --> 06:13.790
I didn't even thinkthat was possible.

06:13.831 --> 06:15.083
[Leah chuckles]

06:16.751 --> 06:20.004
- Daddy's not here.- No?

06:20.088 --> 06:22.632
Well, I'm sure it's justa delay. Hang on one second.

06:22.673 --> 06:24.175
Excuse me, I know you've gotyour hands full.

06:24.258 --> 06:26.552
I just have a UM here. She'ssupposed to be meeting her dad.

06:26.594 --> 06:27.762
Have you heard anything?

06:27.887 --> 06:30.098
Just got a text.Security's backed up.

06:30.098 --> 06:31.808
He'll be here soon. Hopefully.

06:31.849 --> 06:33.726
Security's backed up,so it'll just be

06:33.768 --> 06:35.103
a little bit longer, okay?

06:35.144 --> 06:36.187
No worries.

06:36.312 --> 06:38.940
You've got to catchanother flight, don't you?

06:39.065 --> 06:41.776
I do.I'm sorry, sweetheart.

06:41.818 --> 06:44.028
Just slide me her paperworkand park her in that chair.

06:44.112 --> 06:46.364
- I'll do the hand-off.- 'Okay. Thank you.'

06:47.698 --> 06:49.242
Oh, oh!

06:49.325 --> 06:51.994
- Let me help you.- Oh, come on.

06:57.583 --> 07:00.169
- You see him?- No.

07:02.547 --> 07:04.632
- 'Oh. Here we go.'- 'Um..'

07:04.632 --> 07:06.259
You know what?

07:07.593 --> 07:08.970
I'm feeling pretty exhausted

07:09.095 --> 07:10.471
from losing at hearts to youall day.

07:10.513 --> 07:14.392
So, um, I think I'm just gonnacatch my flight tomorrow.

07:14.475 --> 07:16.435
Are you sure?

07:16.519 --> 07:17.854
Yeah.

07:20.022 --> 07:22.525
I'm telling you,reindeer-powered or not

07:22.650 --> 07:24.777
there is no waythat Santa's sleigh

07:24.819 --> 07:26.070
doesn't have landing lights.

07:26.154 --> 07:27.864
It's gotta be an FAA rule.

07:27.905 --> 07:29.198
[chuckles]

07:29.240 --> 07:31.200
What do you say we goand get some hot chocolate

07:31.325 --> 07:32.827
while we're waitingon your dad?

07:32.827 --> 07:35.079
- Mm? Deal?- Deal.

07:35.830 --> 07:38.332
- Leah!- Daddy!

07:38.374 --> 07:39.625
He-hey..

07:39.709 --> 07:41.210
Hi, monkey.

07:42.712 --> 07:44.672
Mmm! Hey.

07:44.672 --> 07:45.882
- Daddy?- Mm-hm?

07:45.923 --> 07:47.925
- You are late.- I know. I'm sorry.

07:47.967 --> 07:49.302
My lucky pen'snot so lucky today.

07:49.385 --> 07:51.387
I forgot I had it in there,and it kept settin' off

07:51.512 --> 07:53.139
the metal detector.

07:53.181 --> 07:55.099
- Oops.- Daddy's a reporter.

07:55.141 --> 07:56.976
- Oh, is that right?- Uh..

07:57.018 --> 07:59.061
And this is my new friend,Sydney.

07:59.103 --> 08:00.938
'She sat with methe whole flight'

08:00.980 --> 08:03.524
and gave me a front-row seat.

08:03.608 --> 08:05.026
Wow! That was sure nice of her.

08:05.067 --> 08:07.111
(Leah)'And, we played foosballwith peanuts'

08:07.195 --> 08:08.404
and we built a Christmas tree

08:08.446 --> 08:11.616
out of coffee stirrersand sizzle sticks.

08:11.657 --> 08:14.160
We did. Swizzle sticks, we did.

08:14.243 --> 08:16.621
Yeah, it's perfect,I figured as much.

08:16.662 --> 08:18.122
[laughs]

08:18.206 --> 08:20.333
Um, I know this sounds crazy,but I do need

08:20.416 --> 08:22.043
to actually ask youfor a photo ID

08:22.168 --> 08:24.670
before the airlinecan officially release

08:24.754 --> 08:26.422
this little charmer.

08:27.548 --> 08:29.175
Thank you.

08:30.426 --> 08:32.595
"Jonathan Murphy."

08:32.720 --> 08:34.722
- It's official.- Alright.

08:34.804 --> 08:36.224
Thanks so muchfor taking care of Leah.

08:36.265 --> 08:38.808
I mean, the holidays can bekind of a tough time for us.

08:38.851 --> 08:42.355
So...you really put a smileon her face.

08:42.438 --> 08:45.024
Oh, sure. It was my pleasure.She was great.

08:45.066 --> 08:47.527
Leah, you havea Merry Christmas, okay?

08:47.610 --> 08:48.653
You all set, kiddo?

08:48.736 --> 08:50.238
Actually, daddy

08:50.279 --> 08:53.741
Sydney and I were justgoing to get hot cocoa.

08:53.783 --> 08:55.117
Can we still get some?

08:55.243 --> 08:57.912
Well, uh, actually,I have a lot of work to do.

08:57.995 --> 08:59.747
And we got the familycomin' over tonight, so..

08:59.872 --> 09:01.916
Yeah. And I have to geta hotel room, right?

09:02.041 --> 09:04.877
- Daddy, where's Bali?- Bali?

09:04.919 --> 09:07.213
Um, Asia, I think. Why?

09:07.296 --> 09:10.174
'Cause Sydney missed her flightto Bali for me.

09:10.216 --> 09:11.759
Bali? Really?Are you kidding?

09:11.842 --> 09:14.679
- I'm so sorry.- Oh, no. It's okay.

09:14.720 --> 09:16.889
You told me alwaysto say "Thank you"

09:16.973 --> 09:18.099
when people are nice.

09:18.224 --> 09:21.602
Don't we at least owe Sydneya cocoa thank you?

09:21.686 --> 09:23.354
[chuckles]

09:24.939 --> 09:26.732
Yeah, cocoa it is.

09:26.816 --> 09:28.276
No, you reallydon't have to do that.

09:28.401 --> 09:31.946
- Oh, trust me, I do.- He does.

09:31.988 --> 09:33.781
[chuckles]Okay.

09:33.864 --> 09:35.199
You're havin'..You're gettin' a cocoa.

09:35.241 --> 09:38.077
[chuckles]Apparently, I am. Okay.

09:38.786 --> 09:42.081
[instrumental music]

09:51.632 --> 09:54.427
- Yeah?- Okay. All checked in.

09:54.510 --> 09:58.139
This hotel always holds a fewopen rooms for flight crew

09:58.264 --> 10:00.766
which is lucky for usbecause the restaurant

10:00.808 --> 10:02.768
serves the besthot chocolate around.

10:02.852 --> 10:04.353
I'll say.

10:06.564 --> 10:08.107
Mm.

10:11.277 --> 10:13.654
Oh, boy!It might be very good.

10:16.574 --> 10:18.034
Slow down.

10:18.159 --> 10:19.493
Rocket fuel.

10:19.577 --> 10:21.329
(Sydney)'That's okay. She's good.'

10:21.454 --> 10:23.581
- Yeah, I can see her.- Okay.

10:23.664 --> 10:24.790
So, you're a reporter?

10:24.874 --> 10:27.084
Uh, I'm a columnist now,uh, these days

10:27.168 --> 10:28.919
but I used to bean investigative reporter.

10:28.961 --> 10:31.005
Um, then, I needed to workfrom home more

10:31.088 --> 10:33.007
so I started a columnin the paper instead.

10:33.007 --> 10:34.175
Oh, really? What's it called?

10:34.258 --> 10:35.301
It's called "Scouter Stories."

10:35.384 --> 10:37.136
Great excuse for me and Leahto get out

10:37.219 --> 10:39.930
and chase down adventuresall over the city. Pretty cool.

10:39.972 --> 10:42.516
But, right now,I have a new editor, and, um

10:42.516 --> 10:44.852
she wants to use the spacefor ad sales, so I'm like..

10:44.977 --> 10:46.354
If you see beads of sweaton my forehead

10:46.354 --> 10:48.481
it's because I've gotwriter's block and a deadline

10:48.564 --> 10:50.358
for a great Christmas storythis week.

10:50.399 --> 10:51.525
I totally get it.

10:51.650 --> 10:52.818
If I miss a deadline, 300 people

10:52.860 --> 10:54.195
might miss their vacations.

10:54.278 --> 10:58.449
Right. I'm sorry aboutthe whole Bali situation.

10:58.532 --> 10:59.367
Oh, no. It's fine.

10:59.367 --> 11:00.868
I'm sure I can fly out tomorrow

11:00.993 --> 11:02.828
with a few creative connections.

11:02.912 --> 11:04.705
Ah, Christmasin Bali, that's..

11:04.830 --> 11:06.165
- Yeah.- It's cool, but, um..

11:06.248 --> 11:08.542
Are you gonna missa regular Christmas?

11:08.668 --> 11:10.169
Oh, gosh. Not a chance.

11:10.211 --> 11:11.879
No. It's the best timeto travel.

11:12.004 --> 11:14.715
Christmas day,the airports are a breeze.

11:14.757 --> 11:16.509
But caroling and..

11:16.592 --> 11:19.637
...snowball fightsand snow, I mean..

11:19.720 --> 11:21.430
Come on.

11:21.555 --> 11:24.517
I guess Christmasjust isn't really

11:24.558 --> 11:25.810
that big of a deal to me.

11:25.851 --> 11:28.729
And I like how no two daysare ever the same.

11:28.813 --> 11:31.190
I like two days the same,if they're good days.

11:31.273 --> 11:34.860
But don't you miss, like,adventure..

11:34.944 --> 11:36.153
Oh, I think I've gotenough adventure

11:36.237 --> 11:37.822
with this little monkey here.

11:37.905 --> 11:39.031
[chuckles]

11:39.115 --> 11:41.909
So, um,where do you call home?

11:41.909 --> 11:43.327
I live in California.

11:43.411 --> 11:46.038
But, uh, actually,I was born

11:46.122 --> 11:48.416
and lived here in Chicagountil I was six.

11:48.416 --> 11:51.502
- Local girl.- Yeah, I guess.

11:51.544 --> 11:53.421
- What part of the city?- North side, maybe.

11:53.546 --> 11:55.131
- Does that make sense?- Yeah.

11:55.172 --> 11:57.800
But, uh, do you knowwhat school you went to?

11:57.842 --> 11:59.760
Uh..

11:59.844 --> 12:02.138
Any other details?Streets?

12:02.179 --> 12:04.473
Uh, I'm not really sure.Details are kinda hazy.

12:04.515 --> 12:06.225
Do you remember any storesthat you went to?

12:06.308 --> 12:09.437
Sorry, I'm totally grilling you.That's, uh.. Sorry.

12:09.437 --> 12:12.356
Old reporter habits die hard.

12:12.440 --> 12:15.317
No, no, it's fine. I carry gumfor take-off and landing.

12:15.359 --> 12:17.111
- Even when I'm not flying.- Wait a minute.

12:17.153 --> 12:19.113
Um, can't your parentstell you where you lived?

12:19.155 --> 12:21.157
Uh, no. They passed.

12:21.282 --> 12:23.743
Oh, I'm sorry.

12:23.826 --> 12:27.371
That's okay. I grew up withmy grandparents in California.

12:27.413 --> 12:30.040
So, Chicago is pretty mucha blank slate.

12:30.124 --> 12:31.333
It's a great place.

12:31.459 --> 12:33.043
Yeah, I mean,I'd love to see it more.

12:33.127 --> 12:35.546
You know, if I, uh,was ever here for long enough.

12:35.629 --> 12:39.383
Actually, my parents met hereover Christmas time.

12:39.467 --> 12:42.386
- What? Really?- Yeah.

12:42.470 --> 12:43.345
Uh, how?

12:43.512 --> 12:46.015
I don't really knowthe details, actually.

12:46.140 --> 12:47.475
Not even a clue? I mean..

12:47.558 --> 12:50.978
Uh, can you..I'm just desperate for stories.

12:51.103 --> 12:52.605
[chuckles]Especially this week.

12:52.688 --> 12:55.065
But it sounds great.Did your grandparents ever..

12:55.149 --> 12:57.067
Uh, I'd love to help you.

12:57.109 --> 12:59.028
I, um,I know my grandparents said

12:59.153 --> 13:01.697
that they met hereduring college.

13:01.739 --> 13:04.325
And, um.. Oh!

13:04.450 --> 13:05.784
- Actually..- Mm-hm?

13:05.868 --> 13:09.455
Uh, this is from the Christmaswhen they met.

13:09.538 --> 13:12.333
'Uh, yeah, there's picturesof them in here from that time.'

13:12.333 --> 13:15.252
I've always been really curiousabout more of that story.

13:15.336 --> 13:16.796
- But, uh..- Yeah.

13:16.879 --> 13:18.047
I'm sorry, it's..

13:18.088 --> 13:20.174
That's probablytoo much information.

13:20.299 --> 13:21.967
No, no, no.Not enough information.

13:22.051 --> 13:25.221
Um, do you mind?Can I see the photos?

13:25.346 --> 13:27.681
Oh. Uh, no,I'll show them to you.

13:27.765 --> 13:29.975
Hey, don't break iton my account.

13:30.059 --> 13:31.852
There we go.

13:31.977 --> 13:34.188
Uh, that's mom and dad.

13:34.230 --> 13:36.065
Wow! Cool photos.

13:36.190 --> 13:38.692
[cell phone beeps]Oh, sorry.

13:38.776 --> 13:41.862
Uh, the ghostof deadlines future.

13:41.946 --> 13:44.365
I should probably grab Leahand get out of here.

13:44.490 --> 13:46.033
- Yup.- Hey, buddy, you ready?

13:46.158 --> 13:48.369
(Sydney)Hey, little one.

13:48.410 --> 13:51.247
Leah, I feel like I'm alwayssaying goodbye to you.

13:51.372 --> 13:55.209
Then, let's say it inanother language this time.

13:55.209 --> 13:56.710
That's a great idea.

13:56.794 --> 14:00.339
-Arrivederci.█- Ooh, what's that?

14:00.381 --> 14:02.508
I put in for a job postingin Rome

14:02.591 --> 14:04.552
so I've been brushing upon my Italian.

