(Jonathan)'Take it easy,we have to save some of those'

42:34.468 --> 42:36.428
for Christmas morning.

42:36.428 --> 42:37.638
- Daddy?- Yeah?

42:37.763 --> 42:41.016
Sydney isn't going to be hereon Christmas morning.

42:41.100 --> 42:44.270
And then, what if someonehas a gift for her?

42:45.729 --> 42:49.275
You are so sweet and not justbecause you're covered in icing.

42:49.316 --> 42:51.443
'But you don't haveto worry about me, okay?'

42:51.485 --> 42:53.737
What do you say we give somepresents out tomorrow night?

42:53.821 --> 42:56.991
Christmas Eve Eve, right?Start a new tradition.

42:57.032 --> 42:58.367
Sounds great.

42:58.409 --> 43:00.536
Jonathan, can you help mewith the dishes?

43:00.619 --> 43:01.745
Yeah, I got this.

43:02.955 --> 43:06.667
Sydney, want to makea snowman outside?

43:06.792 --> 43:09.795
I might be a little rusty..

43:09.837 --> 43:14.800
...but, um, it's Christmas time,so, what do you say?

43:14.883 --> 43:16.176
Let's go.

43:17.303 --> 43:20.389
Let's make a snowmanten-feet tall.

43:20.431 --> 43:23.976
Oh, or we could makea snow-kid

43:24.059 --> 43:25.144
that's like,about your height.

43:25.227 --> 43:26.895
What do you thinkabout that?

43:26.979 --> 43:30.232
- Let's go.- Okay.

43:31.984 --> 43:34.236
[instrumental music]

43:36.071 --> 43:39.325
[indistinct chatter]

43:46.874 --> 43:48.292
[laughing]

43:48.375 --> 43:49.376
Oh, no!

43:51.003 --> 43:52.588
Kids are readyfor Christmas film fest.

43:52.671 --> 43:55.007
Okay. I just wanna give hera couple more minutes.

43:55.132 --> 43:57.343
Peace! Peace! Truce! Truce!

43:57.468 --> 44:00.346
I haven't seen Leahthis happy in a while.

44:00.429 --> 44:03.724
Yeah. She and Sydneyare having a lot of fun.

44:03.849 --> 44:05.267
I think you have, too.

44:05.309 --> 44:06.852
It's the first Christmasin a while

44:06.977 --> 44:08.520
I've seen you this happy.

44:08.562 --> 44:11.273
Yeah, I've been havinga pretty great week.

44:11.315 --> 44:14.610
Look, you're doingan amazing job with Leah.

44:14.693 --> 44:16.445
You always put her first.

44:16.528 --> 44:19.740
But maybe, it's time you thoughtabout yourself again, too.

44:19.865 --> 44:21.533
Seize the day.

44:21.617 --> 44:23.285
My day is seized

44:23.369 --> 44:26.955
in-between the...bake salesand the brownies

44:27.039 --> 44:28.707
and the birthday parties.

44:28.791 --> 44:30.334
I don't have roomfor more.

44:30.417 --> 44:34.213
When was the last time you wenton a date, last Christmas?

44:34.254 --> 44:37.049
Look, I appreciatethe sisterly advice, but..

44:37.091 --> 44:39.134
But you don't want it.

44:39.968 --> 44:41.512
Exactly.

44:43.806 --> 44:46.475
No, don't throw.Stop it.

44:48.227 --> 44:51.230
I haven't done this since..

44:51.355 --> 44:54.233
Wow! Since I wasprobably about your age.

44:54.233 --> 44:56.568
Like, ten years ago.

44:56.693 --> 44:59.446
Yes!Exactly that.

44:59.488 --> 45:01.907
No, I think it wasa little longer than that.

45:02.032 --> 45:05.035
- Sydney?- 'Yeah?'

45:05.077 --> 45:09.331
Are sky angelslike snow angels?

45:09.373 --> 45:11.041
Hm..

45:11.083 --> 45:13.252
That's a reallygood question.

45:13.293 --> 45:16.755
All I know is that they'reboth really beautiful

45:16.797 --> 45:20.968
whether they're in the snowor up in the clouds.

45:21.093 --> 45:22.761
And I'm an expertin the clouds

45:22.845 --> 45:26.432
because I've spent almosthalf my life up there.

45:26.432 --> 45:29.601
(Jonathan)The cousins are startingthe Christmas movies, honey.

45:29.643 --> 45:33.564
Ooh, I hope they rememberedcaramel popcorn.

45:34.481 --> 45:35.482
Aw..

45:35.524 --> 45:36.525
Thank you.

45:36.567 --> 45:40.154
Oh! Wait!What are you doing to my angels?

45:42.156 --> 45:44.366
Looks like you guysare having some fun.

45:44.408 --> 45:46.618
Yes, I, uh,couldn't have asked

45:46.702 --> 45:49.955
for better Christmas chaperonesfor this week.

45:49.955 --> 45:51.123
Hey, I heard from my editor.

45:51.123 --> 45:52.499
Um, your folks didn't show up

45:52.624 --> 45:53.959
in any ofthe "Nutcracker" programs.

45:54.084 --> 45:55.294
That was a long shot.

45:55.419 --> 45:56.795
And they're notin the archives either.

45:56.837 --> 45:58.922
So, back to square one.

45:59.006 --> 46:00.466
That's okay.

46:01.091 --> 46:02.801
I just made a snow angel

46:02.926 --> 46:04.511
so that is giving mea pretty big

46:04.553 --> 46:06.638
sense of accomplishmentright now.

46:07.848 --> 46:10.058
Johnny, the kids want meto watch movies with them.

46:10.142 --> 46:12.811
Uh, you two mind finishing upthe dishes?

46:13.896 --> 46:16.482
Sure, yeah. We're on it.

46:16.523 --> 46:17.608
[chuckling]

46:18.317 --> 46:20.235
(Jonathan)Nice work today.

46:20.319 --> 46:23.155
You're getting into thatholiday spirit, I see.

46:23.197 --> 46:26.408
[chuckles]I am, I'm..

46:26.450 --> 46:28.243
...actually havinga great time.

46:28.327 --> 46:30.370
Yeah, those snow angelslooked sharp. You know--

46:30.496 --> 46:31.997
I was impressed,I was impressed.

46:32.080 --> 46:33.332
I was..We were all impressed.

46:33.373 --> 46:36.418
It's funny, you know like,Christmases bring back

46:36.502 --> 46:38.337
so many happymemories for me.

46:38.337 --> 46:40.047
Some bittersweet, as well.

46:40.172 --> 46:41.965
- I know what you mean.- Yeah.

46:42.007 --> 46:43.217
Well, I gotta say,this past week

46:43.342 --> 46:45.135
Leah's been so happy,you know?

46:45.219 --> 46:46.512
And I don't think thatthe caroling and the cookies

46:46.595 --> 46:48.305
are just fun, I thinkthat they're also giving her

46:48.388 --> 46:50.224
this sense of stabilityand normalcy

46:50.265 --> 46:52.351
that she reallyhas been needing.

46:52.392 --> 46:53.936
- I understand.- And if I'm being honest, I..

46:54.019 --> 46:56.230
I don't think I'm beingsuch a great dad all the time.

46:56.355 --> 46:57.815
I'm always on a callor a deadline

46:57.898 --> 47:01.193
and trying to be this acecolumnist and this perfect dad

47:01.235 --> 47:03.487
and I'm probablyjust floundering at both.

47:03.570 --> 47:06.365
That is so not true.Are you kidding?

47:06.448 --> 47:09.701
- Just look at the evidence.- The evidence?

47:09.827 --> 47:12.412
What a great kid you have.

47:14.790 --> 47:16.250
You know what?

47:16.291 --> 47:18.377
- I have to thank you.- For what?

47:18.502 --> 47:22.214
For inviting meto be a part of all this.

47:22.297 --> 47:25.759
And, I have a confessionto make.

47:25.884 --> 47:28.053
But dinner around a table

47:28.136 --> 47:30.347
definitely beats room service.

47:31.598 --> 47:36.562
I guess I just forgot, like,how much fun Christmas can be.

47:41.692 --> 47:43.485
- Careful. Sorry.- I'm sorry.

47:43.569 --> 47:45.070
- I'm just gonna--- 'Oh.'

47:45.153 --> 47:47.531
- Oh. Okay.- Actually..

47:47.614 --> 47:49.867
- 'Whoops.'- Oh. Here, did you..

47:49.908 --> 47:53.036
Here, I'll wash.You dry.

47:53.078 --> 47:55.289
- Okay.- 'Sure.'

47:59.585 --> 48:03.130
(Arthur)'Jonathan, Sydney,come here, we've got something.'

48:03.171 --> 48:05.048
- Oh.- Okay.

48:05.090 --> 48:07.676
- Let's go check. Give me that.- No.

48:07.759 --> 48:09.928
No? Come on. Hey!

48:13.140 --> 48:16.518
Okay, so, tech wizard that I am,I managed to scan in

48:16.560 --> 48:18.437
the photosat a higher resolution.

48:18.562 --> 48:22.024
Now, take a look, that's nota ballet outfit she's wearing.

48:22.065 --> 48:23.483
'It's an ice-skating outfit.'

48:23.609 --> 48:25.319
(Sydney)'Wait, ata "Nutcracker" performance?'

48:25.444 --> 48:27.613
Oh, no, no, no. Take a lookat the background here.

48:27.654 --> 48:30.032
You see that "Nutcracker" figureis the same one

48:30.073 --> 48:31.366
'they haveat the Christmas display'

48:31.450 --> 48:32.701
'every year at City Park.'

48:32.743 --> 48:34.244
(Robin)'I know exactly where that is.'

48:34.328 --> 48:35.704
- 'It's just by the ice rink.'- Mm-hm.

48:35.746 --> 48:37.414
- 'Yeah.'- Well, of course.

48:37.456 --> 48:38.916
I mean,it makes really good sense.

48:38.999 --> 48:42.544
- She loved skating.- We're getting warmer here.

48:42.628 --> 48:45.464
Thank you. We're gonna gocheck it out tomorrow, right?

48:45.547 --> 48:47.549
- 'Thanks. Yeah, definitely.'- 'Okay.'

48:47.633 --> 48:49.801
(Leah)I'm gonna head backto the hotel for now.

48:49.843 --> 48:50.886
'But, thank you, Leah.'

48:50.969 --> 48:52.971
I had so much fun playingwith you today.

48:53.096 --> 48:54.931
Thank you so much,sweet girl.

48:55.015 --> 48:56.683
I hope you don't mind

48:56.725 --> 49:00.520
but I've been prayingfor bad weather.

49:00.562 --> 49:01.313
Why?

49:01.438 --> 49:04.566
To keep you here longer,of course.

49:04.650 --> 49:07.152
Come here, you.Thank you.

49:07.277 --> 49:08.654
I'm gonna see you tomorrowthough, okay?

49:08.779 --> 49:10.197
- You walk me out?- Yeah.

49:10.322 --> 49:11.657
Okay. Come on.

49:11.782 --> 49:14.076
- Good work, sweetheart.- Thanks.

49:18.330 --> 49:19.414
(Lorenzo on speaker)'Lesson 10.'

49:19.498 --> 49:21.416
[speaking in foreign language]

49:21.500 --> 49:23.627
[cell phone ringing]Mm.

49:25.504 --> 49:29.007
Kerry, hi.Where are you?

49:29.132 --> 49:30.300
Tulsa. Just landed.

49:30.384 --> 49:31.885
But the better question is,where are you?

49:31.927 --> 49:34.179
- Still in Chicago?- Merrily marooned.

49:34.179 --> 49:37.182
(Kerry)'So, are you stillflying out on Christmas day?'

49:37.182 --> 49:39.017
As far I know..

49:39.017 --> 49:42.479
...three more days to feaston Christmas cookies.

49:42.562 --> 49:45.023
Unless, of course,my flights get cancelled.

49:45.148 --> 49:46.525
So, how are things going?

49:46.566 --> 49:50.362
I'm having a surprisingly goodtime being stranded in Chicago.

49:50.487 --> 49:52.698
Doing what, exactly?

49:52.698 --> 49:55.534
(Sydney)Well, today..

49:55.534 --> 49:57.786
...we made Christmas cookies.

49:57.869 --> 50:01.540
- And I made a snow angel.- You made a snow angel?

50:01.581 --> 50:03.834
You should try it sometime.It's actually quite fun.

50:03.917 --> 50:06.128
Just tell me this,in this little

50:06.211 --> 50:07.838
Chicago Christmas scenario

50:07.921 --> 50:11.508
is there a guyinvolved, perhaps?

50:12.551 --> 50:14.720
(Sydney)No, there is not.

50:14.845 --> 50:17.264
I mean, there's a guy,but it's not like that.

50:17.389 --> 50:18.640
His name is Jonathan.

50:18.724 --> 50:20.559
Mostly, I've just beenhanging out with his family

50:20.642 --> 50:22.060
for, like, the last three days.

50:22.144 --> 50:23.228
Aah! I knew it!

50:23.311 --> 50:24.896
You're, you're fallingfor him, too.

50:24.938 --> 50:27.232
- I can hear it in your voice.- No, I am not.

50:27.315 --> 50:28.442
I'm not falling for anybody.

50:28.567 --> 50:29.901
I'm not even looking to fall

50:29.943 --> 50:31.319
and neither is he.

50:31.403 --> 50:32.696
How's the weather in Tulsa?

50:32.738 --> 50:35.282
Apparently, not as warmas in Chicago.

50:35.323 --> 50:37.075
'Listen, I am,I'm gonna be landing'

50:37.159 --> 50:38.410
in O'Hare late tomorrow night.

50:38.535 --> 50:39.995
On my way home for Christmas,do you wanna

50:40.078 --> 50:41.455
maybe grab a Christmas mocha?

50:41.580 --> 50:44.583
- Yeah, that sounds perfect.- Okay, I'll give you a shout.

50:44.708 --> 50:47.711
- Okay.Ciao, ciao.█- Bye.

50:50.881 --> 50:52.048
Mm.

50:53.258 --> 50:54.259
Green one.

50:54.301 --> 50:56.720
[instrumental music]

50:56.803 --> 51:01.725
Our next stopon our Christmas quest..

51:02.601 --> 51:05.437
...is a Christmas tree farm..

51:08.940 --> 51:14.196
...where, along the pines,we discovered..

51:17.157 --> 51:19.242
Got you covered, dad.

51:26.374 --> 51:29.878
...another breadcrumbin our search.

51:35.967 --> 51:39.096
Wow, look at this.Your family comes through again.

51:39.179 --> 51:40.597
There's our Nutcrackers.

51:40.680 --> 51:42.516
- 'There's our ice rink.'- 'Yeah.'

51:42.641 --> 51:46.645
So, whoever took my mom'sphotograph must've been standing

51:46.645 --> 51:48.522
up on that gazebo, right?

51:48.647 --> 51:51.108
We don't know the whole story,but I'm pretty sure your mom

51:51.191 --> 51:52.275
'skated on that rink.'

51:52.359 --> 51:53.819
I guess, skatingran in the family

51:53.819 --> 51:57.322
'cause my grandma always made metake skating lessons growing up.

51:57.447 --> 52:00.867
They sure look likethey're having fun.

52:00.909 --> 52:02.077
Oh, do they?

52:02.119 --> 52:04.663
I mean, we are hereat an ice rink, right?

52:04.704 --> 52:08.750
It would be a shame for usnot to give it a try.

52:08.792 --> 52:11.253
Oh, I don't thinkthat's a good idea.

52:11.336 --> 52:12.879
Come on, daddy.

52:13.004 --> 52:16.216
What's the matter, you afraidof a little Christmas adventure?

52:16.341 --> 52:19.010
Well, I don't think "Afraid"is a strong enough word.

52:19.094 --> 52:21.179
[whispers]I think we should do it. Yeah?

52:21.263 --> 52:24.015
(Sydney)Let's go. You're in.

52:24.141 --> 52:25.767
Come on!

52:28.270 --> 52:30.772
[Leah yelling]

52:33.108 --> 52:34.401
- Come on!- Wow.

52:34.442 --> 52:36.152
What are you,a professional skater?

52:36.236 --> 52:37.362
It's coming back to me.

52:37.487 --> 52:39.155
- 'Slowly?'- Yeah! Yeah!

52:39.239 --> 52:42.325
Literally, literally skatingcircles around me.

52:42.367 --> 52:43.577
(Sydney)'Not really.'

52:43.618 --> 52:45.704
Look at you, monkey,you're doing great.

52:45.745 --> 52:49.708
Aunty Robin thinks I mighteven be ready for hockey soon.

52:49.708 --> 52:52.419
Oh, thanks a lot, Aunty Robin.

52:52.460 --> 52:54.212
Looks like skatingruns in your family.

52:54.254 --> 52:56.715
Well, you know, one of my veryfirst memories was my mom

52:56.840 --> 52:58.049
taking me to the ice rink.

52:58.133 --> 53:00.302
She'd put me in betweenher legs and spin me around.

53:00.343 --> 53:02.220
You know, we always usedto have so much fun.

53:02.220 --> 53:04.055
Ah, that's great material.

53:04.139 --> 53:06.641
I'd take notes,but I'm afraid I'd face plant.

53:06.725 --> 53:09.603
- Can we take a selfie?- Yeah, you wanna take a selfie?

53:09.728 --> 53:11.229
Just be careful of the otherskaters. Come over here.

53:11.229 --> 53:12.981
Assuming I can stop.

53:13.857 --> 53:16.276
Here, careful,careful, careful.

53:16.401 --> 53:18.320
Are you ready?

53:18.361 --> 53:19.863
- Here we go.- I was stomping.

53:20.697 --> 53:22.407
- Got it.- Yeah!

53:22.532 --> 53:25.702
- Good job, dad.- Good job, dad.

53:30.457 --> 53:32.292
Oh, now you're rubbin' it in.

53:32.334 --> 53:34.169
[chuckling]

53:35.503 --> 53:37.714
Aww. You know what?

53:37.756 --> 53:39.174
The sun's about to set.

53:39.257 --> 53:40.217
You wanna go up and check out

53:40.258 --> 53:41.468
the view from the gazebo?

53:41.509 --> 53:45.180
Oh, get out of these skates?Yes, please.

53:55.315 --> 53:56.900
(Sydney)Hm.

53:58.860 --> 54:00.612
Wow.

54:00.737 --> 54:01.905
Yeah, look at that.

54:01.988 --> 54:03.823
The view is just likefrom the photograph.

54:03.949 --> 54:05.283
(Jonathan)'Yeah.'

54:05.325 --> 54:07.160
(Sydney)'Do you think my dadcould've been'

54:07.285 --> 54:08.203
the one to stand here

54:08.286 --> 54:10.455
and take that photo of my mom?

54:10.497 --> 54:14.167
From this angle, well,I think you might be right.

54:15.710 --> 54:18.964
[instrumental music]

54:21.549 --> 54:23.176
Daddy, listen.

54:23.969 --> 54:27.722
- Dance?- My pleasure.

54:31.476 --> 54:34.771
[instrumental music]

54:37.148 --> 54:39.401
[humming]

54:41.152 --> 54:43.488
(Jonathan)'Mm. Nice.'

54:43.571 --> 54:46.616
Okay, Sydney.Now your turn.

54:46.700 --> 54:51.037
- Aww. I'm good, sweetie.- Dance, you guys!

54:52.706 --> 54:54.082
Hey, monkey.

54:54.165 --> 54:55.834
[laughing]

54:57.002 --> 54:59.838
[clearing throat]Alright.

55:01.381 --> 55:04.467
[music continues]

55:10.390 --> 55:12.225
[chuckling]

55:21.026 --> 55:23.570
Ha-hah.She's having fun.

55:23.695 --> 55:24.946
You know, it's funny.

55:25.030 --> 55:28.700
These past several dayshave sort of felt like..

55:28.825 --> 55:30.535
...finding an unopenedChristmas present

55:30.577 --> 55:33.830
in the closet and gettingto take a peek inside.

55:35.373 --> 55:39.544
When other kids at schoolwould talk about their parents..

55:39.586 --> 55:42.130
...it would always make mewonder about my own.

55:43.131 --> 55:45.383
I mean, even thoughmy grandparents would

55:45.508 --> 55:48.178
would talk aboutmy folks all the time..

55:48.261 --> 55:50.221
...I guess..

55:50.263 --> 55:54.100
...I always felt sort of likea puzzle with a missing piece.

55:54.142 --> 55:57.729
Well, I wish myreporting skills were better.

55:57.771 --> 56:00.190
We haven't figured outhow they actually met yet.

56:00.273 --> 56:02.692
No.

56:02.776 --> 56:06.529
Even if we only know a partof their Christmas story

56:06.613 --> 56:08.281
I feel like there'sa silver lining.

56:08.406 --> 56:09.532
What do you mean?

56:09.616 --> 56:13.369
I only have a coupleof photographs of my parents

56:13.453 --> 56:16.873
and my memories, but I neverimagined that I would be able

56:16.915 --> 56:20.085
to actually standin their footsteps

56:20.210 --> 56:24.172
and feel so close to themat Christmas.

56:24.214 --> 56:28.218
- And do you?- Yeah. I do.

56:29.302 --> 56:33.014
And all while having a blastat the same time.

56:33.098 --> 56:34.933
'Chicago puts on quite a show.'

56:35.058 --> 56:37.602
Whoa, you should seethis town at New Year's.

56:37.644 --> 56:38.770
- Yeah?- Yeah.

56:38.895 --> 56:40.230
Well, stranger thingshave happened.

56:40.313 --> 56:44.400
I never even expectedto be here for this long.

56:47.112 --> 56:49.531
It's interesting to thinkabout how many happy memories

56:49.572 --> 56:52.075
this gazebohas probably seen.

56:55.954 --> 56:58.331
You never know whena new one might happen.

57:00.792 --> 57:02.001
Yeah.

57:03.169 --> 57:05.130
Oh!

57:05.171 --> 57:07.465
It wasn't quite the memoryI was thinking of.

57:07.590 --> 57:09.384
[laughing]Me either.

57:09.467 --> 57:11.553
Ah! Oh! It's on!

57:11.636 --> 57:13.179
Snowball fight!

57:14.139 --> 57:16.224
(Sydney)Leah! Let's flank your dad.

57:16.307 --> 57:19.811
I don't know what that means,but let's do it!

57:19.936 --> 57:21.813
It means that you get himfrom your side

57:21.813 --> 57:23.440
and I'll get him from mine.

57:23.523 --> 57:25.483
Oh, I'm so scared.

57:26.484 --> 57:29.195
Here I come!Here I come.

57:30.989 --> 57:33.199
[screaming]

57:40.874 --> 57:44.127
[instrumental music]

57:54.554 --> 57:55.930
[sneezes]

57:57.098 --> 58:00.268
[instrumental music]

58:00.351 --> 58:01.519
Hi, how are you?

58:01.603 --> 58:03.563
Can I get one coffee please?

58:05.023 --> 58:07.525
Thank you so much.Keep the change.

58:13.448 --> 58:16.492
Hello, sir. You look like youcould use a little warming up.

58:16.576 --> 58:19.787
Oh, thank you, ma'am.This'll sure hit the spot.

58:19.871 --> 58:21.706
You certainly havethe Christmas spirit.

58:21.748 --> 58:23.124
Yes, I do.

58:23.708 --> 58:27.003
[instrumental music]

